Fire station
A fire station has firemen and fire 
engines. When a building catches fire 
the firemen come in their fire engines 
and put out the fire. You can dial 101

We post our letters by putting them 
in a letter-box. The post-man takes 
these letters to the post-office. 
From here the letters are sent to

Diwali
Diwali is the mail festival of 
Hindus . It is the festival of lights. It 
is celebr ated to express happiness 
on Lord Ram's return to Ayodhya 
from the jungles after 14 years. 
People also worship Goddess 
Lakshmi and Lord Ganesh. They 
decorate their houses with diyas RELIGIOUS FESTIV ALS
Eid 
Eid is celebr ated by Muslims on the 
day after Ramz an. The holy mon th of 
Ramz an is a time for fasting. 
On this day people wear new clothes 
and pray in mosques. They also eat a 
special sweet dish called 'Sewain'.and candles. People wear new clothes and exchang e sweets and gifts.We celebr ate festivals with joy and happiness.

Christmas
The birthday of Jesus Christ, 25 
December , is celebr ated as Chris tmas  
day. People decorate Chris tmas trees 
with lights, bells and balls. They sing

Gurupurabs 
It is the f estival of Sikhs . Gurupurab s 
are celebr ated to mark the birthda ys 
of the ten sikh Gurus. On this day 
people offer prayers at Gurdwaras 
and take out processions. They also 
eat 'lang ar' from a common kitchen. 
Holi
It is called as the festival of colour s, Holi 
is a spring festival of Hindus. People 
play with 'Gulal' and colour ed water on 
this day. They sing and dance and offer 
sweets and gujiya  to each other . Ther e 
is a lot of fun on this festival.
HARVEST FESTIV ALS
These festivals are celebr ated to express happiness over a good harvest.
Pongal is the harvest festival of Tamil Nadu. It is 
celebr ated for three days. On the first day, Lord 
Indir a ' The God of Rain' is worshipped. Family feast 
are held. This day is called Bhogi Pongal. On the 
second day, the Sun God is worshipped. This day is 
called Surya Pongal. On the third day, Cow is 
worshipped. This day is called Matnu Pongal.
